FBIS4-1315 "drafr080_cs94013" FBIS-AFR-94-080-S Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Right-Wingers Occupy N. Transvaal Polling Station Right-Wingers Occupy N. Transvaal Polling Station MB2604104794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 1000 GMT 26 Apr 94 MB2604104794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Afrikaans BFN [Special news report] [Text] An explosive has been defused at Ermelo, Eastern Transvaal. Bomb threats have been received in Bloemfontein. A polling station in the Northern Transvaal has been occupied by right-wingers, and special voting in several places delayed due to technical and other problems.
